page.title: 16Weekend in Skegness
page.content: At the weekend I had a great time. On Friday night I went with the Boys' Brigade to archery lessons. To get a gold you have to shoot the arrow into the middle of the board. Austen got twenty golds and I got seventeen. On the last lesson the man said that we would be having a competition. When I got back from archery lessons I went to the caravan site to see my friends. I had supper there and went home. In the evening my brother Simon, Sanchica, Ann-Marie, Samantha and I went to the pictures. We went to see A VIEW TO A KILL. It was a bit far fetched because there was an office that turned into an air balloon. Next Saturday I am going to see Police Academy 2. On Sunday I played football.
